    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Barley Oligopeptide-160 sh-Polypeptide-112 is a fusion peptide of Oligopeptide-160 and sh-Polypeptide-112 produced by barley plants after using either a transient expression system or transgenesis (stable insertion of a copy of a human gene into its DNA). The fusion peptide contains 150 amino acids and may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
